############# Install RSPAMD  ######################

Login to your FreeBSD server: 

ssh afnog@bsdpcX.sse.ws.afnog.org


DISABLE THE FIREWALL FOR NOW

	$sudo pfctl -d
	
	

1. Install Rspamd, Apache and Postfix and enable them
		$sudo pkg install rspamd postfix apache24 nano
		
		$sudo sysrc apache24_enable=YES
		$sudo sysrc postfix_enable=YES
		$sudo sysrc rspamd_enable=YES
		
		
2. Configure Postfix to accept email for your mail domain as follows


Edit Postfix main.cf

	$sudo nano /usr/local/etc/postfix/main.cf

################
	##Add the two domains that this server will receive email for and filter:


	mydestination = yourdomain.afnog.nog-oc.org, bsdpcX.sse.ws.afnog.org
	transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transport # The file to check to route email
	smtpd_milters = inet:127.0.0.1:11332. 		 # How to connect to Rspamd
	milter_default_action = accept.  			 # skip mail without checks if something goes wrong
	milter_protocol = 6 						 # Required when Postfix processes email through other software before accepting in the queue

################


Save and Exit. 

3. Then edit as below replacing with your matching domain and mailservers respectively


	$sudo nano /usr/local/etc/postfix/transport
	
	##Add your afnog.nog-oc.org domain where his mail will be routed to. 
	
	yourdomain.afnog.nog-oc.org  smtp:[pcYY.sse.ws.afnog.org]
	

Save and Exit the file


4. Run postmap against the file you created. This should be done each time you add or remove a domain

	$cd /usr/local/etc/postfix
	$sudo postmap transport
	$sudo newaliases
	$sudo postfix reload

Save and exit and do the next part which is configuring Apache and Rspamd